[
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.1",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Knowest thou the time when the wild goats of the rock bring forth? {or} canst thou mark when the hinds do calve?",
    "hash": "64fd303db8577108d403fd9cbd38c1db9d7cd64243934f5784df3ff6fec8cd89"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.2",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Canst thou number the months {that} they fulfil? or knowest thou the time when they bring forth?",
    "hash": "391ecc702edf405df0c69176932bdcf86688de47f5e054d4de0bcabcbd9940fd"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.3",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "They bow themselves, they bring forth their young ones, they cast out their sorrows.",
    "hash": "180274f344e03eb261ab132b191d2f4e5f62a1dc32104264e12f0e44861ce929"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.4",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Their young ones are in good liking, they grow up with corn; they go forth, and return not unto them.",
    "hash": "489470e5671b60cb511cd61121e6e75c4c949ea237194a91fcc797145233d8dd"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.5",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Who hath sent out the wild ass free? or who hath loosed the bands of the wild ass?",
    "hash": "78d4b5c64757ec2b1b401c5e2bc7a7c30b95f3a31eeda45a4b5c361997228249"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.6",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Whose house I have made the wilderness, and the barren land his dwellings. {barren...: Heb. salt places}",
    "hash": "5daa4aa26de718c0e215e5f9e2ffd9112eeb97920bb7d90be30fbd8ed699c4dc"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.7",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "He scorneth the multitude of the city, neither regardeth he the crying of the driver. {of the driver: Heb. of the exactor}",
    "hash": "89317f3105e66c4892a4b47c04c8c44f000b9c4028068e5d8fbc11a20fe6816b"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.8",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "The range of the mountains {is} his pasture, and he searcheth after every green thing.",
    "hash": "2d6909338b0cc83ff6947d6c08514dd7e2935b884455cd62acdc3cac30075931"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.9",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Will the unicorn be willing to serve thee, or abide by thy crib?",
    "hash": "ffb12d2465be5b84d4ab2c59c118301080ac57e7d564d0cfe3ad79dedd5b407c"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.10",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Canst thou bind the unicorn with his band in the furrow? or will he harrow the valleys after thee?",
    "hash": "2f4fa4679d96c0cd432932b3670d4f0d723ce88bd0c597427500d018391827c7"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.11",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Wilt thou trust him, because his strength {is} great? or wilt thou leave thy labour to him?",
    "hash": "f2cd1efad713729d894aef3e8735fe7bd37cf53f7a95edf1ce1f30cd91171a5e"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.12",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Wilt thou believe him, that he will bring home thy seed, and gather {it into} thy barn?",
    "hash": "2c84ebb7478554802f713b8e60967b152808f27887ef80ccc0a3d1778fde097b"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.13",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "{Gavest thou} the goodly wings unto the peacocks? or wings and feathers unto the ostrich? {wings and...: or, the feathers of the stork and ostrich}",
    "hash": "ce86b4bcbf970d48fdc8c96233c9926dd1daf32651a4048edc2a9b7c4c8ba8c2"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.14",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Which leaveth her eggs in the earth, and warmeth them in dust,",
    "hash": "9e05c3c23ab5560bacfb67f3dbde3a25b3bac8588c54b0784eaef0ebe16fdc4f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.15",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "And forgetteth that the foot may crush them, or that the wild beast may break them.",
    "hash": "0e4350459ce256cfabd9d67fb0725f7915feef1c090de5c991d8b710cb354904"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.16",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "She is hardened against her young ones, as though {they were} not hers: her labour is in vain without fear;",
    "hash": "9bb3412158b9d8d9207602811e7d69c040abc6e44ddf61002f0f93c3e112a20f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.17",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Because God hath deprived her of wisdom, neither hath he imparted to her understanding.",
    "hash": "fe43272413a09e206ab82271b2ba781b929074feaa3993797eb6477208bbd519"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.18",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "What time she lifteth up herself on high, she scorneth the horse and his rider.",
    "hash": "b99c94bb892239af7a1eb36c1aaf3c7b5c06cabb376875227b5b18d82322df71"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.19",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Hast thou given the horse strength? hast thou clothed his neck with thunder?",
    "hash": "fadfa9f8cec457a634de62892502bc1e1575429e41664ce39299b5bc8673217c"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.20",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Canst thou make him afraid as a grasshopper? the glory of his nostrils {is} terrible. {terrible: Heb. terror}",
    "hash": "e4fc263e38de1f8d8cdb114243f644dac0097f469646f8ceff37d502ac256a87"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.21",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "He paweth in the valley, and rejoiceth in {his} strength: he goeth on to meet the armed men. {He paweth: or, His feet dig} {the armed...: Heb. the armour}",
    "hash": "9b3b5e82bc7d0866e3149754c64a258aadf617b7be68e635ffe433bde8c46654"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.22",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "He mocketh at fear, and is not affrighted; neither turneth he back from the sword.",
    "hash": "d29932811bd300902c1485fd06dd84b24c8a7eaa902b3fefd0ee803d68034aab"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.23",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "The quiver rattleth against him, the glittering spear and the shield.",
    "hash": "7f1a775ca3c424c3f697e6f0bb7f2ab7f284fdcc50164f6f0ddf6cfdbe6bf22e"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.24",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "He swalloweth the ground with fierceness and rage: neither believeth he that {it is} the sound of the trumpet.",
    "hash": "874c5fa02d1e3bbffc7795a3f5626f7bf8ca1a95c9a83d70e1015a08debe69a7"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.25",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "He saith among the trumpets, Ha, ha; and he smelleth the battle afar off, the thunder of the captains, and the shouting.",
    "hash": "4202540d257afb751c270ada3aab2db0880a583ada26bb24c8999adcda9a5411"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.26",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "Doth the hawk fly by thy wisdom, {and} stretch her wings toward the south?",
    "hash": "8289e487b40ac5eab78c209577152df496e7bb1981813b0ab5f96d20dffa8d08"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.27",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Doth the eagle mount up at thy command, and make her nest on high? {at...: Heb. by thy mouth}",
    "hash": "983b403601e74067010bf878a745880711a85e84108aefc69f24d3595420981a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.28",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "She dwelleth and abideth on the rock, upon the crag of the rock, and the strong place.",
    "hash": "8e40518ea0606f815c6f1bef3cda2fa95bf5fb3c7bae88e57d963245c036916f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.29",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "From thence she seeketh the prey, {and} her eyes behold afar off.",
    "hash": "8b72f364e85b8ba9db0ad95d375e580147d1ad15f5a9d644fe06a2a57ba7cc7a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.39.30",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 39,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Her young ones also suck up blood: and where the slain {are}, there {is} she.",
    "hash": "d3ba1e2f6604f404fc88ae600308f95a44bcbadf5b9c4137cc2bf314f258ce79"
  }
]